`IPosition` is simply the public API variant of `Node` in this case - a somewhat common if dubious exercise.

How do you make an instance of this type? You don&#39;t. You call something that gets you such a thing and then pass it along. For example, `first()`, which returns an object whose type hierarchy contains at least IPosition&lt;E&gt;.

For example:

```
void test() {
  IPositionalList&lt;String&gt; list = new LinkedPositionalList&lt;&gt;();

  list.addLast(&quot;Hello&quot;);
  list.addLast(&quot;World&quot;);
  IPosition&lt;String&gt; first = list.first();
