You can create a `settings.gradle` in the parent directory. This just associates `GradleProjectA` with `GradleProjectB`. This is the approach used in the [official Gradle docs][1]. It would look like the following:

`ParentDirectory/settings.gradle`

    rootProject.name = &#39;RootProject&#39;
    include &#39;GradleProjectA&#39;, &#39;GradleProjectB&#39;

Then in `GradleProjectB/build.gradle`, you can simply write `implementation project(&#39;:GradleProjectA&#39;)` under dependencies.


  [1]: https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/declaring_dependencies_between_subprojects.html

